 \"The target is to beat the eight medals won at the lastOlympic Gamesand top of their wishlist is the 4x200m men's freestyle relay, a title which GB will be defending.Ben Proudis another hopeful, in the 50m freestyle.\", \"from\": 523, \"to\": 738, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 667, \"end\": 669, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.6336928528659307, \"rank\": 0.5780515414558552, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Once again, eyes will be onKatie Ledeckyas the most successful female swimmer in history.\", \"from\": 740, \"to\": 829, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ariarne Titmus won gold in the 400m freestyle for Australia in Tokyo and Canadian teenager Summer McIntosh is also aiming for victory in what should be an enthralling event.\", \"from\": 830, \"to\": 1003, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 830, \"end\": 844, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ariarne Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\"}, {\"begin\": 880, \"end\": 889, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999979238162903, \"rank\": 8.252561594357534e-07, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 893, \"end\": 898, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.5970051624860416, \"rank\": 0.6750273503195354, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olymp